<br>
DO NOT COME TO RAIDS IF YOU ARE LOOKING TO GAIN EXP!!! Not gonna happen, we will raid for the most part on set times 2 times per week.. sometimes less.. sometimes more... depending on scheduling... If you want experience... you have allllll this other non-raiding time to get it. If there is a /t to the raid leader with a complaint about not getting exp... you will be asked to leave the raid. <br>
<br>
If you cannot get to the raid by the time posted on the board or MoTD ( trust me the times are always there ) DO NOT EXPECT US TO GET YOU THERE... IF you can get to the raid spot yourself without a train, without complications.. and so forth.. you are welcome to join us, however, you will take whatever spot is open in a group if there is one, or you will be in the last group if there are spots open. PLEASE REMEMBER... IT NEVER matters which group you are assigned to... we have a few main members needed for G1 and possibly G2 who know the way to/from objective of raid and the rest of us are loyal helpers. I cannot stress enough that you are not there for experience playing on raids, you are there to pursue large scale mobs for possible drops for you and/or your guildie. <br>
<br>
PLAN on being on most raids at least 4-5 hours at a time... If you cannot stay that long adn DO NOT already have something set up with a porter to get you outta there early, please don't come to that raid.. come to the next one you have more time for. It is by no means fair to the rest of the guild deep in a zone to have to worry about taking one person out / Invest in a gate potion if you can't gate... <br>
<br>
DO NOT continually ask what did he drop? what did it drop? what armor was that?... Whatever drops will be linked in the channel and the numbers and classes to roll will be announced... patience is a virtue <br>
<br>
LISTEN TO YOUR RAID LEADERS.... IF you go AFK, tell your group leader.. group leaders tell raid leaders.... IT is ok to go afk from time to time we are all human, but if we don't know about it we can't help you <br>
<br>
LISTEN TO the INCOMING messages and ASSIST messages This will only increase our ability to kill kill kill all the ugly creatures we deal with... <br>
<br>
Please understand guys that I know that RL emergencies do come up... talk to me if that happens and I will help you to the best of my ability I promise....I also know that we are all Human and make mistakes from time to time.. IT happens.. I do it; we all do it.....I will NOT kick you from a raid if it is a one time accident that you broke a mezz and so on and so forth... We have now got to be more strict however in enforcing these rules.. You will get a WARNING when we see mistakes happen, If you do not improve the behavior after the warning... you will be disbanded from the raid.. simple as that... The people that are listening should not be suffering or hindered by those that don't. <br>
<br>
Have fun, be respectable to those leading large scale raids, we will succeed in the end <br>
<br>
/hugs <br>
<br>
PS.. Dont mess with a high elf <br>
